description:
Job Description:

 * Design and implement automated deployment, system updates, and monitoring solutions to improve operational efficiency and system stability;
 * Manage and optimize cloud infrastructure and services, with a focus on cloud-native environments;
 * Build highly available, scalable, and secure system architectures to ensure continuous and stable business operations;
 * Collaborate with project managers to gather and analyze user requirements, deliver business presentations, and conduct system demonstrations;
 * Guide clients in clarifying needs, support product training, prepare training materials, and lead system introduction sessions;
 * Perform data initialization, system testing, issue tracking, routine system inspections, data backup, and security audits;
 * Provide daily technical support to clients, including user guidance, answering system usage questions, and resolving non-functional issues on-site.




Job Requirements:

 * Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or a related field, or equivalent practical experience;
 * At least 3 years of experience working with Linux operating systems and scripting languages such as Python or Shell
 * Familiarity with major cloud platforms such as AWS, Google Cloud Platform (GCP), or Microsoft Azure;
 * Strong understanding of cloud-native technologies, including Docker and Kubernetes;
 * Proficient in using Git for version control, with solid collaboration and documentation skills.
